<br>
Top-Propellant<br>
Below that-Channel filler<br>
Below that-fission trigger<br>
Below that-Fusion device<br>
Bottom, and casing-reflector etc<br>
<br>
Also It also STM that as a fireball is formed, the fission products would (Initially at any rate) tend to be trapped near the centre since, being large and heavy, they would tend to be stopped fairly quickly by the atmosphere (A bit like Alpha’s) the neutrons and gammas would travel further out before being absorbed to heat. Thus, initially, the fission fragments would be contained within a rising cloud if convecting hot air and plasma.<br>
